Section 1:
1 L.D. 380
2 Date: (Filing No. S- )
3 JUDICIARY
5 STATE OF MAINE
6 SENATE
7 132ND LEGISLATURE
8 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to S.P. 145, L.D. 380, “An Act to Amend
10 Certain Laws Regarding Gender-affirming Health Care Services”
11 Amend the bill by striking out the title and substituting the following:
12 'An Act to Require Parental Consent for Gender-affirming Hormone Therapy'
13 Amend the bill by striking out everything after the enacting clause and inserting the
14 following:
15 'Sec. 1. 22 MRSA §1508, as enacted by PL 2023, c. 413, §1, is repealed.'
16 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
17 number to read consecutively.
18 SUMMARY
1199 This amendment, which is the minority report of the committee, replaces the bill and
2200 changes the title. The amendment repeals the provision of law that establishes a process
2211 by which a minor who is at least 16 years of age and who is mentally and physically
2222 competent to give informed consent may consent to gender-affirming hormone therapy.
Page 1 - 132LR0675(02)
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT
